I've fixed the issue with images not displaying after app restart. The problem was that the app was storing image URIs directly in the SharedPreferences, but these URIs were temporary content URIs that would become invalid after the app restarted.

Here's what I did to fix the issue:

1. Added a persistent image storage solution in the MainActivity:
 - Created a `saveImageToInternalStorage` function that copies selected images to the app's internal storage directory
 - When an image is picked, it's now saved to internal storage and a file URI is returned

2. Updated all screens that display images to properly handle both content and file URIs:
 - Added proper error handling for URI parsing
 - Added fallback to default images when URIs can't be loaded
 - Improved the reliability of image loading by using try-catch blocks

3. Made sure the AdoptionFormScreen uses the new persistent storage method when selecting images

These changes ensure that your images will be properly stored in the app's internal storage and will persist across app restarts. The app now uses file URIs that point to the app's internal storage directory, which remain valid even after the app is closed and reopened."}]}]}
